This paper deals with clustering algorithms, which are commonly used in machine learning and data analysis. Specifically, it focuses on penalized k-means algorithms for finding the correct number of clusters in a dataset. This topic is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). However, given the emphasis on machine learning and data analysis, cs.LG and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories, followed by cs.CL, cs.CV, and cs.DS.
